This visualisation shows the relation between the TotalSteps and
Calories burned in the dataset activity. There is a clear positive
correlation, so it can be observed, those who have a higher total step
count will see their expenditure of calories increase. But a very high
step count shows diminishing returns as calorie burned begins to slow
down. The slight curvature in the line further highlights this.

